<body hidden="true">
<span class="pAPIKeysBing" style="display: none;">
	<h2>How to get Bing translator API keys</h2>
	<p>To get more Bing API keys, follow <a href="http://blogs.msdn.com/b/translation/p/gettingstarted1.aspx">this instructions</a></p>
	<h3>In a nutshell</h3>
	<ol>
		<li>Register for an account on <a href="https://datamarket.azure.com/home/">Windows Azure Marketplace</a> with a Microsoft account.</li>
		<li><a href="https://datamarket.azure.com/dataset/bing/microsofttranslator">Sign up for the Microsoft Translator API</a>  using your registered account. Sign up for the free one ($0.00).</li>
		<li>Register your application on <a href="https://datamarket.azure.com/developer/applications/register">Windows Azure Marketplace.</a> This step can be repeated several times to get several <b>Client IDs</b> and <b>Client Secrets</b>. <b>DO NOT ABUSE!!!</b></li>
		<li>Get the <b>Client ID</b> and <b>Client Secret</b> for your registered application.
			<ol>
				<li>Fill out the <b>Client ID</b>, and <b>Name</b> fields.</li>
				<li>The <b>Client Secret</b> field is already completed for you. <b>DO NOT CHANGE IT.</b></li>
				<li>Fill out the <em><b>Redirect URI</b></em> field with any valid URL that uses https, for example <em>https://microsoft.com</em>. This field is not used by the Microsoft Translator API.</li>
				<li>You can also leave the <em><b>Enable subdomain access</b></em> checkbox unchecked, as Translator doesnt use it.</li>
			</ol>
		</li>
		<li>The <b>Client ID</b> and <b>Client Secret</b> fields are the API keys used by Multi Translator button.</li>
	</ol>
</span>
<span class="pAPIKeysYandex" style="display: none;">
	<h2>How to get Yandex translator API keys</h2>
	<p>Get more Yandex API keys <a href="https://tech.yandex.com/key/form.xml?service=trnsl">here (English)</a> or <a href="https://tech.yandex.ru/key/form.xml?service=trnsl">here (Russian)</a></a></p>
	<h3>In a nutshell</h3>
	<ol>
		<li>Visit the provided link and register a Yandex account (or use one of the available social services).</li>
		<li>Once you successfully finish creating the Yandex account, you can visit the link provided at the beginning several times to create several API keys. <b>DO NOT ABUSE!!!</b></li>
		<li>Once you have several API keys, you can use them to replace the ones that come with <b>Multi Translator</b> button by default. <b></b></li>
	</ol>
</span>
<div class="important-notes">
	<h3>Important notes</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>API keys are only used by the translator panel. The page translator uses a totally different translation method.</li>
		<li>The API keys are stored into a preference. Keep your API keys backed up outside the application in case you reset <b>Multi Translator's</b> preferences.</li>
		<li><b>NEVER</b> make your API keys public!!! The whole purpose of going to the trouble of getting your own API keys is that the only one <em>consuming</em> their limits is you and nobody else.</li>
	</ul>
</div>
</body>
